#!/bin/bash
# Simple MVP pipeline for converting chat formats to SkogAI format
# Usage: ./convert <format> <input_file>

set -e

FORMAT="$1"
INPUT="$2"

if [ -z "$FORMAT" ] || [ -z "$INPUT" ]; then
    echo "Usage: ./convert <format> <input_file>"
    echo "Formats: claude, goose, gptme, aichat"
    exit 1
fi

case "$FORMAT" in
    claude)
        jq -c -f jq-utils/extract-claude-content.jq "$INPUT" | \
        jq -f jq-utils/clean-tool-calls.jq | \
        jq -f jq-utils/flatten-content-arrays.jq | \
        jq -f jq-utils/normalize-timestamp.jq | \
        jq '{eid: (.uuid // "unknown"), from: (if .role=="user" then "claude-user" else "claude" end), to: (if .role=="user" then "claude" else "claude-user" end), content, "created-at": .timestamp, parent: .parentUuid}'
        ;;
    goose)
        jq -c -f jq-utils/extract-goose-simple.jq "$INPUT" | \
        jq -f jq-utils/normalize-timestamp.jq | \

#!/bin/bash
# Simple MVP pipeline for converting chat formats to SkogAI format
# Usage: ./convert <format> <input_file>

set -e

FORMAT="$1"
INPUT="$2"

if [ -z "$FORMAT" ] || [ -z "$INPUT" ]; then
    echo "Usage: ./convert <format> <input_file>"
    echo "Formats: claude, goose, gptme, aichat"
    exit 1
fi

case "$FORMAT" in
    claude)
        jq -c -f jq-utils/extract-claude-content.jq "$INPUT" | \
        jq -f jq-utils/clean-tool-calls.jq | \
        jq -f jq-utils/flatten-content-arrays.jq | \
        jq -f jq-utils/normalize-timestamp.jq | \
        jq '{eid: (.uuid // "unknown"), from: (if .role=="user" then "claude-user" else "claude" end), to: (if .role=="user" then "claude" else "claude-user" end), content, "created-at": .timestamp, parent: .parentUuid}'
        ;;
    goose)
        jq -c -f jq-utils/extract-goose-simple.jq "$INPUT" | \
        jq -f jq-utils/normalize-timestamp.jq | \
        jq '{eid: (.id | tostring), from: (if .role=="user" then "goose-user" else "goose" end), to: (if .role=="user" then "goose" else "goose-user" end), content, "created-at": (.timestamp | todate), parent: null}'
        ;;
    gptme)
        jq -c -f jq-utils/extract-gptme-conversation.jq "$INPUT" | \
        jq '{eid: ("gptme-" + (now | tostring)[0:10]), from: (if .role=="user" then "gptme-user" else "gptme" end), to: (if .role=="user" then "gptme" else "gptme-user" end), content, "created-at": .timestamp, parent: null}'
        ;;
    aichat)
        yq -o=json "$INPUT" | \
        jq -c -f jq-utils/extract-aichat-messages.jq | \
        jq '.[] | {eid: (.index | tostring), from: (if .role=="user" then "aichat-user" else "aichat" end), to: (if .role=="user" then "aichat" else "aichat-user" end), content, "created-at": (.timestamp | todate), parent: null}'
        ;;
    *)
        echo "Unknown format: $FORMAT"
        echo "Supported: claude, goose, gptme, aichat"
        exit 1
        ;;

No, I didn't just concatenate them raw. The pipeline:

1. **Converts each format properly** using `merge-all-chats.sh` which runs the jq conversion pipelines
2. **Claude** uses the Python merger to handle the already-converted files 
3. **Then** concatenates the converted skogchat files (which are already in the same format)

Each file gets properly converted to skogchat format FIRST (with proper EIDs, timestamps, from/to fields), THEN they're concatenated.
